Source: foundry-emulators-vintage
Section: metapackages
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Foundry Linux <packages@foundrylinux.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.7.0
Homepage: https://foundrylinux.org/
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: foundry-emulators-vintage
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
 vice,
 atari800,
 fbzx,
 mame-extra
Description: vintage home-computer emulators with bundled ROMs (multiverse)
 Emulators whose .deb ships non-redistributable ROMs or BIOS data.
 Users opt in explicitly; this metapackage is NOT preinstalled in any
 image we publish. Requires Ubuntu multiverse component to be enabled.
 .
   * vice         Commodore 64 / 128 / VIC-20 / PET / Plus/4 (KERNAL+CHAR+BASIC ROMs)
   * atari800     Atari 8-bit XL / XE / 5200 (OS ROMs)
   * fbzx         ZX Spectrum (ROM)
   * mame-extra   MAME sample files and debugging ROMs (mixed licensing)
 .
 Enable multiverse with: sudo add-apt-repository -y multiverse
